yer? Could you suggest one—who would not be too expensive? I have been referred to a man called Max Chopnik, 9 East 40 Street—have you ever heard of him?

Finally, would you be so very kind and have the Russian copy of INVITATION TO A BEHEADING which I mailed you, sent to my son?





Very cordially,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: VICTOR C. THALLER1

CC, 1 p.





Goldwin Smith Hall

Ithaca, NY.

September 17, 1958

